<br>
No disrespect, but how is this different from Not Roleplaying?<br>
<br>
Are dark elves just Blue people?  Halflings just Short people?  Erudites just dark skinned egghead people?  If so what is the point?<br>
<br>
I am not suggesting that there is no room for deviation, or that you have to regurgitate everything that SOE says, but in order to play a Role with a large group, certain ground rules need to be respected.<br>
<br>
For example, Norrath is the name of world we play in.  There is nothing stopping you from calling Qwertyville...  Just like there is nothing stopping you from calling Planet Earth Planet Ghora in RL, but then you need to expect the same response.<br>
<br>
Also, I think that the general gist of Races and Cultures should be respected.  No, you do NOT have to say that all DEs are mindless rabid creatures of Hate, but I do expect you to agree that most are from Neriak, and they live in a society where Innoruk is highly regarded, and they are generally enemies with Elves and Halflings, and reasonably cordial with Ogres and Trolls.<br>
<br>
So yes, there can be a DE Troll Hater, Halfling lover, but you would be uncommon at best.<br>
<br>
