Officer of Clan Twisted</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mysteweave>Mysteweave</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/21/03 2:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FV lost</span><hr size=1> Kaneer, I think what you said made a lot of sense.<br>
<br>
To me: EQ is a lot more like the muds I also played back 10-11 years ago. The world does not change. It remains the same. It is backdrop to the character interactions we have with one another. We are the poeple who choose how we RP, we decide how our character is going to behave and feel and react. <br>
<br>
Coded limitations restrict RP. I believe this firmly. I played a Moo based on Dragonriders of Pern that had code for everything. Instead of simply role-playing feeding your dragon, you actually had to perform a set of coded tasks to do it. Very boring and very tedious. Your dragon could sicken and look weak without you allowing this. This is not RP to me.<br>
<br>
RP is where you choose what happens to you and how you react to other people's interactions. <br>
<br>
If you do not want to play evil as a dark elf, there is no reason you should -- however, there will be other people who DO RP as you being evil, and that is their perogative. That is because you cannot force your vision of RP on anyone else. A person has a right to RP an assumption about your character whether or not they know the facts. They can also choose to see the light and realize you are not how they percieved you to be. (Ie; Say a RL person is a bigot and hates all people of a certain race, regardless of their personalities, it is the same thing as in the game).<br>
<br>
Syrienne can RP how she wants. She can RP that she is, though of an evil raced, a good person -- however she will have to prove, via RP to people who do not believe this, that it is so. *shrug*<br>
<br>
RP folks, is what you make of it. No set of rules or instructions is going to make that any better and could in fact, make it worse. <br>
<br>
I can go on any server of EQ and RP. The thing is: here on FV, more people are going to RP -back- at me because more people here lean toward the idea that we should RP than would normally occur on another server.<br>
<br>
If you want pure RP folks, please, go find a Mush. These are text only games and most of them are very immersive and full of RP. If you don't see a theme you like -- make up one and host your own mush and advertise about it on other mushes.<br>
<br>
Thats what everyone else does.<br>
<br>
However. I have no problem RPing a mix of RP and doing OOC on EQ. I have a lot of fun here, and there's no pressure to do one or the other, and I am happy because there are folks I can RP with, and folks I can just bash around on things with and not have to worry bout RP for a while.<br>
<br>
